The President has declared a major disaster in the State of Oregon and authorized federal aid to assist in the recovery efforts from a severe winter storm and flooding that occurred from December 14-17, 2016. The funding will be available to state, tribal, and local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also receive funding. Dolph A. Diemont has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or fema-news-desk@fema.dhs.gov.